# Recursion vs Iteration: 
1. Things done recursively can also be done iteratively.
2. Iteration does not use recursive call stack space (better space complexity).
3. Recursion has both an ascending(calling) and descending(returning) phase, iteration has only ascending phase.
4. Recursion has better readability, easy to write (especially for complex questions).



# Recurrence Relation:
Expresses the solution of a problem as a function of the solutions to smaller instances of the same problem.



# Practice Problem 1:--------------------------------------
Factorial —>
function factorial(n){
    if(n===1){
        return 1;
    } 
    return factorial(n-1)*n;
}
let result=factorial(5); 
console.log("result::", result); // 5*4*3*2*1=120


# Practice Problem 2:--------------------------------------
Fibonacci series—>
function fibonacci(n){
    if(n===1){
        return 1;
    } 
    if(n===0){
        return 0;
    }
    return fibonacci(n-1)+fibonacci(n-2);
}
let result=fibonacci(5); 
console.log("result::", result); // 0 1 1 2 3 5


